egorize the perceived twenty-first-century failures of masculinity, family, and the American Dream, Restivo shows how the televisual cinematic has the potential to change the ways viewers relate to and interact with the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aPopular culturezUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aTelevision seriesxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aTelevision serieszUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Television / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2019z978311069632540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478003441zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478003441423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478003441.jpg  a978-3-11-069632-5  DUK eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles